							<div class="post">As I said, if you daisy-chain two 4-digit modules you&#039;ll just have to ignore digits 4-7.&nbsp; To display &quot;1234.5678&quot; you&#039;d have to:<br /><br /><div class="codeheader">Code:</div><div class="code">LedControl lc=LedControl(12,11,10,2);&nbsp; // Two modules daisy-chained<br /><br />void setup() {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lc.setScanLimit(0, 4);&nbsp; &nbsp;// Use only 4 digits on the first module<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lc.setScanLimit(1, 4);&nbsp; &nbsp;// Use only 4 digits on the second module<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lc.setDigit(0, 0, 1, false);<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lc.setDigit(0, 1, 2, false);<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lc.setDigit(0, 2, 3, false);<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lc.setDigit(0, 3, 4, true);&nbsp; // Decimal point<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lc.setDigit(1, 0, 5, false);<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lc.setDigit(1, 1, 6, false);<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lc.setDigit(1, 2, 7, false);<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lc.setDigit(1, 3, 8, false);<br />}<br /></div></div>
